(This is the user's son) I think it was a great game! I don't think it's the best of the three, but I do find it fun and scary. It's a lot harder than the two first ones, but I never found myself stressing nearly as hard as I did in the previous (FNaF2 Night 6). Two things, though, the phantom animatronics force me off the camera WAY too fast. I swear I turn to a camera to see BB staring and get 0.0001 seconds to react. Surley enough, BB jumpscares me, making me have to reboot ventilation, completely throwing me off. The other thing doesn't have anything to do with the gameplay, but I thought it was worth mentioning: the extras menu needs both mini-games and jumpsares. One more thing, aggressive nightmare mode is really hard and I understand that. But even when my ventilation is fine, I can see the "phantom" Springtrap. You know, the second one that appears when ventilation is out. I think I have him contained in cam 10 with the vent blocked off, but nooooo, he's right outside my door somehow! He killed me, obviously. So, it's a good game and I recomend it to people who want to be scared, but I don't to people who are new to the series. Great job, Scott, keep it up!

So I see that many of you are saying that night three is impossible. On night three, Springtrap mainly uses the vents, so all you need to do is get him into camera 07, then go to the vent and block the vent that is connected to camera 07. Just keep your eye on those two cameras and whenever he moves, he should go into that specific vent, then when he disappears, you just need to call him back to that vent. Wash, rinse and repeat and you will beat night 3. Then you will see that night 4 is impossible.
